CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "Local Members Of The Consistory - Local members of Consistory 4, the host for the three-day meeting of Prince Hall Masons, are, seated, left to right: Grand Inspectors General James F. Bryant, Wilbur C. Douglas, Joseph W. Givens and James E. King. Back row: Maj. A. Green, Sublime Prince; Henry C. Bailey, III, Commander-in-Chief; Paul Morris, Thomas Lee, Daniel L. Burrell, James T. Barnes, Harry J. Keene, James A. Washington, Joseph D. Hudson and Marshall S. Johnson. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fourteen 33 degree Masons, seated from left: General James F. Bryant, Wilbur C. Douglas, Joseph W. Givens, and James E. King; standing from left: Major A. Green, Henry C. Bailey, III, Paul Morris, Thomas Lee, Daniel L. Burrell, James T. Barnes, Harry J. Keene, James A. Washington, Joseph D. Hudson, and Marshall S. Johnson, gathered around bench in Fort Pitt Hotel interior for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33-Degree Masons
